==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homoiousian
<hw>Ho`moi*ou"si*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, <?/,
of like substance; <grk>"o`moios</grk> + <grk>o'ysi`a</grk> the
substance, being, essence.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of
the semi-Arians of the 4th century, who held that the Son was of like,
but not the same, essence or substance with the Father; -- opposed to
<xex>homoousian</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homoiousian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Homoiousian
<hw>Ho`moi*ou"si*an</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
Homoiousians, or their belief.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

